Note: Integration Testing
Process called "run_cross_module_integration_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Boolean]:
    Print "Starting Cross-Module Integration Tests..."
    
    Let integration_results be Dictionary with:
    
    Note: Test Core-Skills Integration
    Print "Testing Core-Skills Integration..."
    Let core_skills_result be test_core_skills_integration()
    Set integration_results["core_skills"] to core_skills_result
    
    Note: Test Skills-Tasks Integration
    Print "Testing Skills-Tasks Integration..." 
    Let skills_tasks_result be test_skills_tasks_integration()
    Set integration_results["skills_tasks"] to skills_tasks_result
    
    Note: Test Goals-Tasks Integration
    Print "Testing Goals-Tasks Integration..."
    Let goals_tasks_result be test_goals_tasks_integration()
    Set integration_results["goals_tasks"] to goals_tasks_result
    
    Note: Test Swarm-Coordination Integration
    Print "Testing Swarm-Coordination Integration..."
    Let swarm_coordination_result be test_swarm_coordination_integration()
    Set integration_results["swarm_coordination"] to swarm_coordination_result
    
    Note: Test Tasks-Coordination Integration
    Print "Testing Tasks-Coordination Integration..."
    Let tasks_coordination_result be test_tasks_coordination_integration()
    Set integration_results["tasks_coordination"] to tasks_coordination_result
    
    Note: Test Network-All Modules Integration
    Print "Testing Network Integration with All Modules..."
    Let network_integration_result be test_network_all_modules_integration()
    Set integration_results["network_all"] to network_integration_result
    
    Return integration_results

Process called "test_core_skills_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that agent identity properly integrates with skill management
    Let agent_identity be create_agent_identity with name as "IntegrationTestAgent" and description as "Agent for integration testing"
    Let skill_manager be create_skill_manager()
    
    Note: Test skill assignment to agent
    Let basic_skill be create_test_skill()
    Set skill_manager to define_skill_with_validation with manager as skill_manager and skill as basic_skill
    Set skill_manager to assign_skill_to_agent with manager as skill_manager and agent_id as agent_identity.id and skill_name as basic_skill.name
    
    Note: Verify integration
    Let agent_skills be get_agent_skills with manager as skill_manager and agent_id as agent_identity.id
    Return agent_skills contains basic_skill.name

Process called "test_skills_tasks_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that skills can be converted to executable tasks
    Let skill be create_test_skill()
    Let task_conversion_result be convert_skill_to_task with skill as skill
    
    Note: Verify task was created with skill properties
    Return task_conversion_result.task_created and task_conversion_result.task.description contains skill.name

Process called "test_goals_tasks_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that goals properly decompose into executable tasks
    Let goal be create_test_goal()
    Let task_conversion_result be convert_goal_to_tasks with goal as goal
    
    Note: Verify tasks were created
    Return task_conversion_result.tasks_created is greater than 0

Process called "test_swarm_coordination_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that swarm operations use coordination protocols
    Let swarm be create_test_swarm()
    Let coordination_context be create_coordination_context_for_swarm with swarm as swarm
    
    Note: Test leader election integration
    Let election_result be elect_swarm_leader with swarm as swarm
    Return election_result.leader_elected is not equal to ""

Process called "test_tasks_coordination_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that distributed tasks use coordination for execution
    Let task be create_distributed_test_task()
    Let coordination_result be coordinate_task_execution with task as task
    
    Return coordination_result.coordination_successful

Process called "test_network_all_modules_integration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that network layer properly supports all module communications
    Let network_test_results be list containing
    
    Note: Test network supports agent discovery
    Add test_network_agent_discovery() to network_test_results
    
    Note: Test network supports skill distribution
    Add test_network_skill_distribution() to network_test_results
    
    Note: Test network supports swarm communication
    Add test_network_swarm_communication() to network_test_results
    
    Note: Test network supports coordination protocols
    Add test_network_coordination_protocols() to network_test_results
    
    Note: All network integration tests must pass
    For each result in network_test_results:
        If not result:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Performance Benchmarking
Process called "run_performance_benchmarks" returns Dictionary[String, Number]:
    Print "Starting Performance Benchmarks..."
    
    Let benchmark_results be Dictionary with:
    
    Note: Core Module Benchmarks
    Print "Benchmarking Core Module Performance..."
    Set benchmark_results["core_agent_creation_ops_per_sec"] to benchmark_agent_creation()
    Set benchmark_results["core_state_transitions_ops_per_sec"] to benchmark_state_transitions()
    
    Note: Skills Module Benchmarks
    Print "Benchmarking Skills Module Performance..."
    Set benchmark_results["skills_execution_ops_per_sec"] to benchmark_skill_execution()
    Set benchmark_results["skills_sandbox_overhead_percent"] to benchmark_sandbox_overhead()
    
    Note: Swarm Module Benchmarks
    Print "Benchmarking Swarm Module Performance..."
    Set benchmark_results["swarm_consensus_time_ms"] to benchmark_swarm_consensus()
    Set benchmark_results["swarm_scalability_max_agents"] to benchmark_swarm_scalability()
    
    Note: Tasks Module Benchmarks
    Print "Benchmarking Tasks Module Performance..."
    Set benchmark_results["tasks_scheduling_throughput_ops_per_sec"] to benchmark_task_scheduling()
    Set benchmark_results["tasks_workflow_execution_time_ms"] to benchmark_workflow_execution()
    
    Note: Coordination Module Benchmarks
    Print "Benchmarking Coordination Module Performance..."
    Set benchmark_results["coordination_leader_election_time_ms"] to benchmark_leader_election()
    Set benchmark_results["coordination_conflict_resolution_time_ms"] to benchmark_conflict_resolution()
    
    Return benchmark_results

Note: Configuration Validation
Process called "run_configuration_validation_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Boolean]:
    Print "Starting Configuration Validation Tests..."
    
    Let validation_results be Dictionary with:
    
    Note: Test valid configurations
    Set validation_results["valid_core_config"] to validate_core_configuration()
    Set validation_results["valid_skills_config"] to validate_skills_configuration()
    Set validation_results["valid_swarm_config"] to validate_swarm_configuration()
    Set validation_results["valid_goals_config"] to validate_goals_configuration()
    Set validation_results["valid_tasks_config"] to validate_tasks_configuration()
    Set validation_results["valid_coordination_config"] to validate_coordination_configuration()
    
    Note: Test invalid configurations
    Set validation_results["invalid_config_rejection"] to test_invalid_configuration_rejection()
    
    Note: Test configuration compatibility
    Set validation_results["config_compatibility"] to test_configuration_compatibility()
    
    Return validation_results

Note: End-to-End System Testing
Process called "run_end_to_end_system_tests" returns Boolean:
    Print "Starting End-to-End System Tests..."
    
    Note: Test complete agent lifecycle with real scenarios
    Let e2e_results be list containing
    
    Note: Scenario 1: Multi-agent collaborative task completion
    Print "E2E Test: Multi-agent collaborative task completion..."
    Add test_multiagent_collaborative_task() to e2e_results
    
    Note: Scenario 2: Agent failure and recovery
    Print "E2E Test: Agent failure and recovery..."
    Add test_agent_failure_recovery() to e2e_results
    
    Note: Scenario 3: Dynamic swarm reconfiguration
    Print "E2E Test: Dynamic swarm reconfiguration..."
    Add test_dynamic_swarm_reconfiguration() to e2e_results
    
    Note: Scenario 4: Complex goal decomposition and execution
    Print "E2E Test: Complex goal decomposition and execution..."
    Add test_complex_goal_decomposition() to e2e_results
    
    Note: Scenario 5: Network partition handling
    Print "E2E Test: Network partition handling..."
    Add test_network_partition_handling() to e2e_results
    
    Note: All E2E tests must pass
    For each result in e2e_results:
        If not result:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Production Readiness Assessment
Process called "assess_production_readiness" that takes test_summary as SystemTestSummary returns Number:
    Let readiness_score be 0.0
    Let max_score be 100.0
    
    Note: Test coverage weight (40%)
    Let coverage_weight be 0.4
    Let coverage_score be test_summary.overall_success_rate multiplied by 100.0
    Set readiness_score to readiness_score plus (coverage_score multiplied by coverage_weight)
    
    Note: Performance weight (25%)
    Let performance_weight be 0.25
    Let performance_score be calculate_performance_score with benchmark_results as test_summary.benchmark_results
    Set readiness_score to readiness_score plus (performance_score multiplied by performance_weight)
    
    Note: Integration weight (20%)
    Let integration_weight be 0.20
    Let integration_score be calculate_integration_score with integration_results as test_summary.integration_test_results
    Set readiness_score to readiness_score plus (integration_score multiplied by integration_weight)
    
    Note: Configuration weight (10%)
    Let config_weight be 0.10
    Let config_score be calculate_configuration_score with config_results as test_summary.configuration_validation
    Set readiness_score to readiness_score plus (config_score multiplied by config_weight)
    
    Note: Critical failures penalty (5%)
    Let critical_penalty_weight be 0.05
    If length of test_summary.critical_failures is greater than 0:
        Let penalty be (length of test_summary.critical_failures multiplied by 10.0)
        Set readiness_score to readiness_score minus penalty
    
    Note: Ensure score is within bounds
    If readiness_score is greater than max_score:
        Set readiness_score to max_score
    If readiness_score is less than 0.0:
        Set readiness_score to 0.0
    
    Return readiness_score

Note: Master Test Execution
Process called "run_all_agent_module_tests" returns SystemTestSummary:
    Print "========================================="
    Print "Starting Comprehensive Agent Module Testing"
    Print "========================================="
    
    Let master_start_time be get_current_timestamp()
    Let test_environment be setup_master_test_environment()
    
    Let module_results be list containing
    
    Note: Execute all individual module tests
    Add run_core_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_skills_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_swarm_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_goals_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_tasks_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_coordination_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_capabilities_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_network_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_config_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_hierarchical_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_lifecycle_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_metrics_module_tests() to module_results
    Add run_registry_module_tests() to module_results
    
    Note: Execute integration tests
    Let integration_results be run_cross_module_integration_tests()
    
    Note: Execute performance benchmarks
    Let benchmark_results be run_performance_benchmarks()
    
    Note: Execute configuration validation
    Let config_validation_results be run_configuration_validation_tests()
    
    Note: Execute end-to-end system tests
    Let e2e_system_result be run_end_to_end_system_tests()
    
    Let master_end_time be get_current_timestamp()
    Let total_execution_time be master_end_time minus master_start_time
    
    Note: Calculate summary statistics
    Let total_modules be length of module_results
    Let total_tests_run be 0
    Let total_tests_passed be 0
    Let total_tests_failed be 0
    Let critical_failures be list containing
    Let performance_summary be Dictionary with:
    
    For each module_result in module_results:
        Set total_tests_run to total_tests_run plus module_result.tests_run
        Set total_tests_passed to total_tests_passed plus module_result.tests_passed
        Set total_tests_failed to total_tests_failed plus module_result.tests_failed
        
        If module_result.success_rate is less than 0.95:  Note: Less than 95% success
            Add (module_result.module_name plus " has low success rate: " plus module_result.success_rate) to critical_failures
        
        Set performance_summary[module_result.module_name] to module_result.execution_time_ms
    
    Let overall_success_rate be (total_tests_run is greater than 0 and (total_tests_passed divided by total_tests_run) or 0.0)
    
    Note: Create comprehensive test summary
    Let test_summary be SystemTestSummary with:
        total_modules_tested as total_modules
        total_tests_run as total_tests_run
        total_tests_passed as total_tests_passed
        total_tests_failed as total_tests_failed
        overall_success_rate as overall_success_rate
        total_execution_time_ms as total_execution_time
        critical_failures as critical_failures
        performance_summary as performance_summary
        configuration_validation as config_validation_results
        integration_test_results as integration_results
        benchmark_results as benchmark_results
        production_readiness_score as 0.0  Note: Will be calculated next
    
    Note: Assess production readiness
    Set test_summary.production_readiness_score to assess_production_readiness with test_summary as test_summary
    
    Note: Print comprehensive results
    Print "========================================="
    Print "Comprehensive Test Results Summary"
    Print "========================================="
    Print "Total Modules Tested: " plus total_modules
    Print "Total Tests Run: " plus total_tests_run
    Print "Total Tests Passed: " plus total_tests_passed
    Print "Total Tests Failed: " plus total_tests_failed
    Print "Overall Success Rate: " plus (overall_success_rate multiplied by 100.0) plus "%"
    Print "Total Execution Time: " plus total_execution_time plus "ms"
    Print "Production Readiness Score: " plus test_summary.production_readiness_score plus "/100"
    
    If length of critical_failures is greater than 0:
        Print "CRITICAL FAILURES DETECTED:"
        For each failure in critical_failures:
            Print "  - " plus failure
    
    Print "========================================="
    
    Note: Integration test results
    Print "Integration Test Results:"
    For each integration_name and result in integration_results:
        Let status be (result and "PASS" or "FAIL")
        Print "  " plus integration_name plus ": " plus status
    
    Note: Performance benchmark results
    Print "Performance Benchmark Results:"
    For each benchmark_name and value in benchmark_results:
        Print "  " plus benchmark_name plus ": " plus value
    
    Note: End-to-end system test result
    Let e2e_status be (e2e_system_result and "PASS" or "FAIL")
    Print "End-to-End System Tests: " plus e2e_status
    
    Print "========================================="
    
    Note: Cleanup
    Let cleanup_result be cleanup_master_test_environment()
    
    Return test_summary

